    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-10-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tyler</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Ray</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-10-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Tyler reports that he has been requested to inform the Department that the
                    Shah of Persia telegraphed to the Crown Prince at Tabriz to arrest the murderers
                    of Mr. Labaree immediately.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
